2star  aWidely regarded as a premier journal dedicated to the study of Syriac, Hugoye: Journal of Syriac Studies was established in 1998 as a venue devoted exclusively to the discipline. An organ of Beth Mardutho, the Syriac Institute, the journal appears semi-annually and will be printed in annual editions. A peer-reviewed journal, Hugoye is a respected academic source for up-to-date information about the state of Syriac studies and for discovering what is going on in the field. Contributors include some of the most respected names in the world of Syriac today. This is Volume 4 of the journal from 2001.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn multiple languages.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Feb 2021) 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Orthodox.2bisacsh1 aEl-Souriany, Fr. Bigoul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFathi-Chelhod, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarrak, Amir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarvey, Susan A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInnemée, Karel C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiraz, George A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiraz, George, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLehto, Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMakhlouf, Avril M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPenn, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmidt, Andrea B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTakahashi, Hidemi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVan Rompay, Lucas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146